  "solution": {
    "answer": "$H_0(\\mathbb{R}P^\\infty) \\cong \\mathbb{Z}$;\\quad $H_k(\\mathbb{R}P^\\infty) \\cong \\mathbb{Z}/2$ for $k$ odd, $k \\geq 1$;\\quad $H_k(\\mathbb{R}P^\\infty) = 0$ for $k$ even, $k \\geq 2$.",
    "steps": [
      "The CW structure on $\\mathbb{R}P^\\infty$ has one cell in every dimension $\\geq 0$. Chain complex (each $C_k = \\mathbb{Z}$): $\\cdots \\xrightarrow{0} \\mathbb{Z} \\xrightarrow{\\times 2} \\mathbb{Z} \\xrightarrow{0} \\mathbb{Z} \\xrightarrow{\\times 2} \\mathbb{Z} \\xrightarrow{0} \\mathbb{Z} \\to 0$.",
      "For even $k \\geq 2$: $d_k = \\times 2$ and $d_{k+1} = 0$. $H_k = \\ker(\\times 2)/\\operatorname{im}(0) = 0$.",
      "For odd $k \\geq 1$: $d_k = 0$ and $d_{k+1} = \\times 2$. $H_k = \\ker(0)/\\operatorname{im}(\\times 2) = \\mathbb{Z}/2$.",
      "$H_0 = \\mathbb{Z}$ (one connected component, since every $\\mathbb{R}P^n$ is connected).",
      "Note the key difference from the finite case $\\mathbb{R}P^{2m}$: there is no top cell to give a $\\mathbb{Z}$ in top homology; the pattern $\\mathbb{Z}/2$ in all odd degrees continues indefinitely."
    ]
  },
